  <discussion>Tortula leucostoma and T. guepinii were considered by W. C. Steere (1939c) to be
        probably subspecies of T. hoppeana (as Desmatodon latifolius). This species differs from T.
        hoppeana largely by the tapering leaf with piliferous costa, and perhaps the somewhat
        shorter seta.</discussion>
